<i>adverb</i>: 중대히 [중ː대히], 엄숙히 [엄수키], 심각히 [심ː가키], 된통 [된ː통/뒌ː통], 단단히 [단단히], 깊이 [기피], 깊숙이 [깁쑤기] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>중대히 [중ː대히]</dt><br>
<dd>seriously</dd><br>
<dd>몹시 중요하고 크게.</dd><br>
<dd>With a lot of importance and magnitude.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>엄숙히 [엄수키]</dt><br>
<dd>1. solemnly; gravely; seriously</dd><br>
<dd>의식이나 분위기 등이 무겁고 조용하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of a ceremony, atmosphere, etc., being heavy and quiet.</dd><br>
<dd>2. solemnly; gravely; seriously</dd><br>
<dd>말이나 태도 등이 무겁고 점잖게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of a speech, attitude, etc., being heavy and refined.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>심각히 [심ː가키]</dt><br>
<dd>seriously; severely</dd><br>
<dd>상태나 정도가 매우 심하거나 절박하거나 중대하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a state in which a state or degree is very severe, urgent, or important.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>된통 [된ː통/뒌ː통]</dt><br>
<dd>hard; seriously</dd><br>
<dd>아주 심하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Very severely.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>단단히 [단단히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. hard</dd><br>
<dd>사물이 어떤 힘에 의해 모양이 변하지 않게.</dd><br>
<dd>(an object) Hard enough not to be changed by a certain force.</dd><br>
<dd>2. hard; solidly</dd><br>
<dd>약하거나 무르지 않고 빈틈이 없이 튼튼하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Evenly solid, not weakly or softly.</dd><br>
<dd>3. firmly</dd><br>
<dd>속이 꽉 차서 야무지고 실속이 있게.</dd><br>
<dd>Fully, firmly, and practically.</dd><br>
<dd>4. tightly; firmly</dd><br>
<dd>느슨하지 않고 튼튼하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Strongly, not loosely.</dd><br>
<dd>5. surely; strongly</dd><br>
<dd>뜻이나 생각이 흔들림 없이 강하게.</dd><br>
<dd>(one's will or thought maintained) Strongly, without being shaken.</dd><br>
<dd>6. seriously; severely</dd><br>
<dd>보통보다 더 심하게.</dd><br>
<dd>More severely than normal.</dd><br>
<dd>7. surely</dd><br>
<dd>확실하게 제대로.</dd><br>
<dd>Done surely.</dd><br>
<dd>8. strongly</dd><br>
<dd>일의 기본 바탕이 튼튼하게.</dd><br>
<dd>(the ground for something made) Strongly.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>깊이 [기피]</dt><br>
<dd>1. deeply; deep</dd><br>
<dd>위에서 밑바닥까지 또는 겉에서 속까지의 거리가 멀게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of the length from top to bottom, or from outside to inside being long.</dd><br>
<dd>2. prudently; cautiously</dd><br>
<dd>생각이 가볍지 않고 신중하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of thinking carefully, not carelessly.</dd><br>
<dd>3. deeply; seriously</dd><br>
<dd>수준이 높거나 정도가 심하게.</dd><br>
<dd>At a high level or to an excessive degree.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>깊숙이 [깁쑤기]</dt><br>
<dd>1. deeply; deep</dd><br>
<dd>위에서 밑바닥까지 또는 겉에서 속까지의 거리가 아주 멀게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a state of the distance from top to bottom, or from the outer limit to the center being very long.</dd><br>
<dd>2. deeply; seriously</dd><br>
<dd>수준이 높거나 정도가 심하게.</dd><br>
<dd>At a high level or to an excessive degree.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>